categories.strCategoryDescription: Beef is the culinary name for meat from cattle, particularly skeletal muscle.
Chicken is a type of domesticated fowl, a subspecies of the red junglefowl. It is one of the most common and widespread domestic animals.
Dessert is a course that concludes a meal. The course usually consists of sweet foods, such as confections.
Lamb, hogget, and mutton are the meat of domestic sheep (species Ovis aries) at different ages.
General foods that don't fit into another category

Pasta is a staple food of traditional Italian cuisine, with the first reference dating to 1154 in Sicily.

Pork is the culinary name for meat from a domestic pig (Sus scrofa domesticus). It is the most commonly consumed meat worldwide,[1].
Seafood is any form of sea life regarded as food by humans. Seafood prominently includes fish and shellfish.
A side dish, sometimes referred to as a side order, side item, or simply a side, is a food item.

Veganism is both the practice of abstaining from the use of animal products, particularly in diet.
Vegetarianism is the practice of abstaining from the consumption of meat (red meat, poultry, seafood.
Breakfast is the first meal of a day. The word in English refers to breaking the fasting period of the previous night.
The domestic goat or simply goat (Capra aegagrus hircus) is a subspecies of C. aegagrus domesticated from the wild goat of Southwest Asia and Eastern Europe.
